==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inscrutable
<hw>In*scru"ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inscrutabilis</ets> : cf. F. <ets>inscrutable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Scrutiny</er>.]</ety> <def>Unsearchable;
incapable of being searched into and understood by inquiry or study;
impossible or difficult to be explained or accounted for satisfactorily;
obscure; incomprehensible; <as>as, an <ex>inscrutable</ex> design or
event</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is not in man⟦br⟧
To yield a reason for the will of Heaven⟦br⟧
Which is <qex>inscrutable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Waiving a question so <qex>inscrutable</qex> as this.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inscrutableness</ent>⟦br⟧
